commentary: Murtagh to Shafiqullah, OUT good length outside off, pushes it out to covers and they take off for a single. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but Ireland's fielders do not seem too excited. He drags the bat but Rashid has been caught short of his crease. This is an important strike. Rashid was well-set and could have powered them to a strong finish. Now, they have been hurt in that regard. Double-wicket maiden and what a time for that - 43rd over of the innings

commentary: Gulbadin Naib to Joyce, 1 no ball what a poor sequence of cricket this is. Back of a length ball at middle stump, he swings across the line lazily, gets a top-edge that hangs up for extra cover who runs in and puts down a sitter. It was a no-ball, of course, so there's not a cricketer on this field right now who can say anything about it. Shafiq was the fielder who took it too easy. Had at least a few seconds to take it after getting under it, but his effort was lazy too. Clipped his fingertips and went to ground. Looked up and the umpire was there, signalling a no-ball

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Wilson, FOUR runs and that's the game for Ireland. Full and on the fifth-stump channel and that does it for Ireland. Drilled through covers and he has placed that so well. Wide of the sweeper cover fielder and into the deep extra cover boundary
